# Wayfare Backend

## API

- Entry: `api/main.py` — lifespan wires pool, Redis, LLM, LangGraph
- Routers: `api/routers/` — traditional search + `/concierge/stream` (SSE)
- All SQL in `api/repository.py` — hybrid retrieval (filters + pgvector + PostGIS) in one query
- Settings via pydantic `api/config.py` — required: `DATABASE_URL`, `OPENAI_API_KEY`; optional models have defaults
- CORS is open (`allow_origins=["*"]`) for Vercel frontend

## Ingestion

- Run: `make seed` or `python -m ingestion`
- Cities from `CITIES` env (lowercase paths under `data/`)
- Stages are idempotent (`ON CONFLICT` upserts); schema stage enables extensions
- `SUMMARY_MAX_LISTINGS` caps review-summary LLM cost for demo seeds

## Database

- Custom image: `docker/db/Dockerfile` (PostGIS + pgvector) — do not use Render managed Postgres
- City values in DB use `city.title()` → `"Lisbon"`, `"Barcelona"` (match frontend/API params)
- Local dump: `docker compose exec db pg_dump -U postgres -Fc -f /tmp/seed.dump travel` then `docker compose cp`

## Agents

- Graph: `api/agents/graph.py` — intent → retrieval → review | itinerary
- Use env models (`INTENT_MODEL`, `SYNTHESIS_MODEL`, `EMBEDDING_MODEL`); default `gpt-4o-mini`
